title: Grateful Dead Live at Greek Theatre, Univ. of California on 1982-05-23
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi DR-1/Dolby B) -> Sound Devices 744T (24bit/48k) -> Adobe Audition v3.0 -> Samplitude Professional v11.1 -> FLAC/16
description:
Set 1

Shakedown Street-> Promised Land, They Love Each Other, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Loser-> Little Red Rooster, Ramble On Rose, Let It Grow

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Samson & Delilah, Ship of Fools, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums*-> The Other One-> Stella Blue-> I Need A Miracle-> Casey Jones, E: Satisfaction, E: Brokedown Palace

*Miked a Harley Davidson Motorcycle during drums

reviews.review_text:
Oh Yea! It's hard to say what events transpire in order to love a few songs on one particular show but...
I'm ready at this point in time to declare this TLEO and the Other One as among the best versions of each, let me throw-in the Ship of Fools as well.  

These three shows starts out good, get better, then even better!!!

FTY ! i am so grateful for the work you did here!! this was one of the best experiences i ever had at a show and it's dynamite to be able to re-listen.

not only that, turns out to have been a kickass show. kick. ass.

excellent Shakedown St!

best LLR ever played. when the band was really all into it this was an awesome tune. (and not if not) Brent throws a curveball about halfway in, adding his own verse. a must-listen track.

there's awesome ambient dialogue on a bunch of tracks... at about 4:30 into SB.someone was talking about someone "just got busted". it really gives an immersive, you-are-there feel. and yet sound quality still manages to be top-notch throughout.
